# Frontend Testing Rules

## Both Unit & Integration

- Use `data-testid` for expectations instead of text locators; add them to components when needed
- `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for setup and cleanup to prevent test pollution
- Don't import `describe`, `it`, `expect`, `vi`, `beforeEach`, `afterEach` from `vitest` — they are available globally

## Unit Tests

- 100% coverage; cover all business logic and requirements from the ticket
- Minimal mocks — return only what the test requires, no logic inside mocks
- Use spies to verify function calls and prop passing to inner components without rendering the component
- Avoid validating `data-testid` prop passing, translation keys, and constants

## Integration Tests

- Test complete user workflows and component combinations
- Test through the public interface — any path is reachable through the rendered component tree; see [ADR-004](../../doc/adr/004-api-level-integration-tests-as-sole-integration-layer.md)
- Keep all project dependencies real — mock only 3rd party libs with browser-only behaviour, inline in the test file, not globally
- If a project dependency cannot be kept real, create a minimal mock that returns only what the 
test requires
- Avoid duplicating logic already covered in unit tests; focus on component interactions

## Form Testing Patterns

### Standalone Forms
- Render with all data (rich scenario)
- Render with minimal data (only if different from above)
- Handle API error (if applicable)

### Multistep Forms
- Happy path with all data
- Happy path with minimal data (only if different from above)
- Preserve data when navigating between steps
- Handle API error (if applicable)
- Handle form validations and proceed
